Pre-Game Insights: Estonia and Slovakia aim to start their UEFA Nations League C campaign positively.
Estonia has recently had friendly victories but struggles in competitive matches.
Slovakia is recovering from their Euro 2024 heartbreak and has shown competitiveness.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Estonia's recent form includes four friendly wins and a Nations League triumph in 2022-23.
Slovakia has a history of competitive performances, including a close Euro 2024 loss.
The match is the first for both teams in the 2024-25 Nations League campaign.
Others: The match is at A. Le Coq Arena in Tallinn at 7:45 pm UK time.
Estonia's possible starting lineup includes Vallner, Schjonning-Larsen, and Tamm.
Slovakia's possible starting lineup features Dubravka, Vavro, and Schranz.
